Russian President Vladimir Putin signed a law on the introduction of administrative responsibility for violation of the period and procedure for payment for goods (works, services) in the implementation of procurement for state and municipal needs.
This law is designed to solve a very acute problem of failure to fulfill their obligations by customers in the implementation of state and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation when entrepreneurs could not receive payment for already executed state and municipal contracts, was ubiquitous.
At the same time, the President of Russia instructed the Prosecutor General's Office of the Russian Federation to take the problem for special control.
Because the businessmen themselves could not cope with unscrupulous customers who concluded contracts not supported by financing, in every possible way tried to evade the accepted obligations on payment and included illegal conditions in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, in the interests of protecting the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public orders, the prosecutor's office has made 9.7 thousand. According to the results of their consideration, 4.5 thousand were brought to disciplinary responsibility. officials, administrative - 533, 75 materials were submitted to the investigative bodies for the organization of procedural inspections, 46 of them criminal cases were initiated.
As a result, the debt to entrepreneurs in the amount of more than 66 billion rubles was repaid.
And these huge sums were not accumulated as a result of non-payment of multibillion-dollar contracts.
To fabulous debts led numerous, systematic delays in payment of services to entrepreneurs for much more modest amounts.
This is a characteristic case.
The head of the small company won a competition for the provision of services for social transportation for several million rubles.
The man invested all his working capital, fully fulfilled his obligations, but he did not receive the money in time.
The result is a growing financial lump of wage, taxes, loans, which would lead to bankruptcy if the entrepreneur did not seek help from the prosecutor's office.
Now in a number of regions, the problem has been minimized as much as possible.
Nevertheless, as of the first half of 2017, the total amount of debt under state and municipal contracts identified by prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation amounted to about 27.4 billion rubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical values, the prosecutor's office operates in the mode of manual anti-crisis management.
The Prosecutor General personally conducts visiting meetings with representatives of the local authorities, which deal with all violations and measures opened by prosecutors to immediately eliminate them.
Such operational meetings have already been held in Yaroslavl and Yekaterinburg this year.
The implementation of the Federal Law No. 189-FZ "On Amendments to the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offences in the Establishment of Administrative Disorders of Public Customers for violation of the term and procedure for payment of goods (works, services) in the implementation of procurement to ensure state and municipal needs," which was signed by the President of Russia last week, will be able to improve the payment discipline of public customers.
The draft law was developed by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia at the initiative of the Prosecutor General's Office.
The new law will complement the Code of Administrative Offences of the Russian Federation, which provides for a fine of 30 thousand. up to 50,000. for violation by the official of the customer of the term and procedure for payment for goods, works and services in state and municipal procurement.
And if the official has already been subjected to administrative punishment for a similar offense, then he will be disqualified for a period of one to two years.
All prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation have already received instructions to ensure the application of these legislative novels in practice.
