The order and places of the oath will be determined by the President
Where and how new Russian citizens will swear allegiance to the Russian Federation, the President will determine - such amendments to the second reading in the relevant law were developed by the State Duma Committee on Legislation and State Construction.
A week ago, the deputies planned to directly determine the procedure for taking the oath in the law.
From the ceremonial oath will be released children under the age of 18, as well as incapacitated, follows from the amended text of amendments to the bill "On citizenship of the Russian Federation" (there is "Izvestia"), which the Committee will consider on July 11 before the second reading at its meeting.
The idea of taking an oath when entering Russian citizenship instead of formally signing documents, President Vladimir Putin supported on June 6 during a meeting with the speaker of the state Duma Vyacheslav Volodin.
The deputies formalized this idea in the form of an amendment to the second reading of the bill, providing for the cancellation of the decision to issue citizenship to those who were subsequently convicted of a number of crimes of a terrorist or extremist nature: for example, for public appeals to terrorism or its public justification in the media or on the Internet. 2 st. 205.2 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation), as well as for the theft of an aircraft, train or water transport, but only if this act is related to terrorism. 4 st. 211 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation).
According to the bill, his logic was as follows: by drawing up documents for citizenship, a person is signed under the promise to comply with Russian legislation - getting on the path of extremism, he violates this promise.
The draft law in April was submitted to the State Duma by the leaders of the Duma factions Vladimir Vasilyev ("United Russia"), Gennady Zyuganov (CPRF), Vladimir Zhirinovsky (LDPR), Sergei Mironov ("Fair Russia") and the speaker of the State Duma Vyacheslav Volodin.
On May 19, the deputies adopted it in the first reading.
Last week, the State Duma Committee on State Construction and Legislation approved the text of the bill for the second reading, but now it has been reworked again.
Now it says that the order of taking the oath will be established by the President of the Russian Federation.
Earlier, parliamentarians were going to describe the procedure directly in the law "On citizenship of the Russian Federation," indicating that the ceremony should be held in a solemn atmosphere in front of the state emblem and the flag of Russia in the presence of the representative of the Ministry of Internal Affairs.
However, from the text of the bill it was not clear where such an event should take place - a list of places where it is possible to place the coat of arms of the Russian Federation, is regulated by the relevant federal constitutional law.
These include the courts, the cabinets of heads of state bodies of subjects, municipalities, judges, prosecutors, heads of federal executive bodies, etc.
Most likely, it could be the registry offices.
To declare a solemn oath that those who want to obtain Russian citizenship will be after officials check their documents.
But the Russian passport will be received only after he takes the oath, it follows from the revised text.
A week ago, the draft said that the oath should precede the signing of the decree.
The updated text says that Russia will be swingn from the age of 18, not from the age of 14.
There is a rule that will be released from the oath of incapacitated or limitedly capable, as well as those who cannot pronounce, read or sign the oath.
In addition, the President of the Russian Federation has the right to exempt from this procedure and "other persons,"
Also in the updated bill prescribed a special procedure for admission to Russian citizens of Ukrainians, who are considered native speakers of the Russian language.
They will have to officially renounce Ukrainian citizenship by submitting an application to the authorized body of Ukraine.
A notarized copy of the application will need to be handed over to Russian officials.
Refusal of "other" citizenship, as now, will not be required, if it is provided for by an international treaty or if it is impossible "for reasons not controlled by the person."
The corresponding amendment to the law was proposed by a group of deputies, including the first vice-speaker of the State Duma Ivan Melnikov (CPRF), Natalia Poklonskaya, Pavel Krasheninnikov and Airat Farrahov (all - "United Russia").
I think many of you know that getting a certificate from Ukraine is unrealistic, it is simply impossible.
Accordingly, a lot of people are waiting for the decision of their fate on the citizenship of the Russian Federation, - explained the head of the Duma Committee on state construction and legislation Pavel Krasheninnikov (EP).
In addition, the text clarifies that the restrictions on the occupation of certain positions for foreigners will not apply to those who have refused in writing of "other" citizenship and passed the previous passport in the Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russia, but "for reasons beyond his control" he did not cease to be considered a citizen of another country.
Now foreigners are forbidden to hold positions in the municipal service, to be hired for facilities and organizations whose activities are related to ensuring the security of Russia.
Also, a person with dual citizenship or a residence permit of another country cannot become a deputy of the State Duma or a member of the Federation Council.
It is planned that the law should enter into force on September 1, 2017, by that time, the necessary by-laws should be ready.
