"If they kill your speech, they will win," it says.
"So never shut up."
"This is a direct quote from the letter she wrote to me," says the artist who welcomes us from Philadelphia.
"I still have goosebumps on my skin when I talk about it."
Manning hasn't seen the exhibition personally - as it was visionary depicted in the comics - but when she comes, she'll be greeted with masks in the center of the room, her own gumfish, gathered like crowds of protesters.
This is also done intentionally, as is everything at the exhibition up to a height (5"2, Manning's height), on which the genetic haplogroups were drawn with a pencil.
"I'd have hung them on the walls before, but now I wanted them to look like a crowd of people," says Dewey Harborg about the portraits.
