Disabled Anton Mamaev was fined
The Moscow City Court commuted the punishment of the wheelchairman Anton Mamaev from four and a half years in prison to a fine of 200 thousand. The rub.
Earlier, by the decision of the Timiryazev court, the convicted person was released from the pre-trial detention center.
At the same time, the Moscow City Court confirmed that the accused is a criminal, since he organized a robbery and kidnapping of a motorcoal from a former special forces fighter.
