In addition, the court applied st. 64 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation, according to which it is possible to impose punishment below the lower limit.
As for the assistant to Mamaev Vasily Serozhtanov, the court did not establish the circumstances that would be the basis for changing the category of gravity and changing the sentence.
Anton Mamaev himself said that he remained dissatisfied with the decision of the Moscow City Court.
I'm disappointed with the court's decision.
The only legal solution would be an excuse, intends to continue to fight for justice.
His lawyer Andrei Orlov did not rule out the appeal of the verdict in the cassation instance of the Moscow City Court and the Supreme Court.
"We will use all the levers up to the European Court of Human Rights," he told RIA Novosti.
