After the immobilized disabled person was placed in the pre-trial detention center, the Public Chamber, the Prosecutor General's Office, the Commissioner for Human Rights under the President Tatiana Moskalkova joined the case.
As a result, in mid-July Anton Mamaev was released from the pre-trial detention center by the decision of the same Timiryazev court.
The defense, in turn, appealed the decision of the first instance in the Moscow City Court.
