Electricity is cheaper for residents and for commodity producers of Buryatia
The efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryatia (Eastern Siberia) to establish fair tariffs for consumers of electricity are beginning to bear fruit.
From September 1, the cost of low voltage electricity for industrial recipients has been reduced by 25%.
Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country in accordance with the Decree of the Government of the Russian Federation "On Amendments to the Rules of the Wholesale Electric Power and Capacity Market and the Combined Prototype Balance of Production and Supply of Electric Power (Power) within the Unified Energy System of Russia by Subjects of the Russian Federation" (from 17.07.2017. No. 842) established indicative prices for electricity and capacity for industrial consumers of the Republic of Buryatia.
As a result, the cost of electricity for Buryat commodity producers is reduced by a quarter, which will greatly facilitate the life of small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the leaders of the republic have outdated the thresholds of Moscow cabinets in futile attempts to equal the region in tariffs with the neighboring Irkutsk region with a cascade of hydroelectric power plants on Angara, flowing from Baikal, the main catchment area for which is Buryatia.
And only this year's progress began.
In March, the tariffs for electric energy for the population of the republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles/kWh to 3.93 rubles/kWh, or 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by the decision of the federal government in the List of territories of price zones of the wholesale market, for which the features of the functioning of the wholesale and retail markets are established, the turn of industrial consumers is established.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, since the population of the Irkutsk region pays for a kilowatt / hour of 1.01 rubles.
But no one dares to name at least the approximate date of the new tariff moves in the direction of the downward for Buryatia.
