In Russia, there will be two new territories of advanced socio-economic development - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk."
The relevant resolutions of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOR on the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia have been determined.
In the city, where 15 thousand people live, there will be a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, as well as the minimum amount of capital investments of residents, the minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities in which the TOR "Abaza" will operate a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activities, for example, include crop, livestock, food production, soft drinks and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise of LLC "Abakansky mine."
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia has fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of the TOR.
The authorities of the Orenburg region also did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, a territory of advanced socio-economic development will also be created.
This will allow to diversify the economy of the single-industry town, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of Ural Steel JSC, as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities, in which the new TOR will operate a special legal regime for entrepreneurs, includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the monotowns of the Orenburg region, which received the status of TOR.
Recall that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges that are created to attract investment to improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOR can be allocated the following: income tax in the amount of not more than 5% for the first five years, and at least 10% over the next 5 years, social contributions in the amount of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free customs zone, preferential regime of connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rates on rent.
